.TH atof 3 (date) "Linux man-pages (unreleased)"
.SH NAME
atof \- convert a string to a double
.SH LIBRARY
Standard C library
.RI ( libc ,\~ \-lc )
.SH SYNOPSIS
.nf
.B #include <stdlib.h>
.P
.BI "double atof(const char *" nptr );
.fi
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.BR atof ()
function converts the initial portion of the string
pointed to by
.I nptr
to
.IR double .
The behavior is the same as
.P
.in +4n
.EX
strtod(nptr, NULL);
.EE
.in
.P
except that
.BR atof ()
does not detect errors.
.SH RETURN VALUE
The converted value.
